text.tspan: Set to "Yes" to enable custom numbers.
Will also make all options appear.
All four sections (Order Numbers, Invoice
Numbers, Shipment Numbers and Credit
Memo Numbers) have exactly the same
configuration.
The number format is the most
important setting of the module: A string,
where [...] indicates a variable (see the
docs for a list of all available variables)
and # indicates the running counter.
Typical examples are:
[year]/# (counter within the year)
INV-# (global counter with prefix)
[year]-[countrycode]/# (counter within
year and country)
Installations with multiple stores only:
Select whether all stores should the same
counters or use their own counters for
each website and/or store.
Most installations are fine with the default
setting "Use all counters across all stores".
Choose whether you want one counter
(global, with or without reset) or multiple
concurrent counters:
One counter without reset: counts up
even if the number has other values
New counter for each year/month/day:
Counts within each year/month/day,
even if the number has other values
or does not contain the year
Separate counter for each format value:
Allows multiple concurrent counters,
indicated by all variables used in the
format
Custom counter name:
The most general case. Allows you to
to have concurrent counters, depending
on variables that are not in the format.
Counter padding: If the counter value
has less digits than this number, it is left-
padded with 0s. E.g. a counter of '23' will
be padded to '000023' if padding is set to
6. If the counter's length is larger than this
value, no relevant digits will be cut off.
The default value 0 means that there is no
automatic padding.
Increment for the counter. Whenever a
number is generated, the counter will
be increased by this value. Typically you
want to use 1.
